<h2>About the Course</h2>
<p>
  A 3-hour intensive delivered across 2 Zoom sessions, designed to give Zouk DJs the tools to build seamless, energetic
  sets.
</p>
<p>Originally scheduled: November 7 & 14, 8:30–10pm ET</p>

<h2>Curriculum</h2>
<ol>
  <li>
    <h3>Music Structure Analysis</h3>
    <p>
      Understanding phrase structure, sections, and how Zouk music is built so you always know where you are in a track.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>Transition Timing</h3>
    <p>When to transition — reading the room, tracking energy, and choosing the right moment.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>Transition Techniques</h3>
    <p>The mechanics of smooth transitions: EQ, volume curves, beat matching, and phrase matching.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>Musical Mashups</h3>
    <p>Layering tracks creatively to create unexpected moments on the dance floor.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3>Energy Management</h3>
    <p>Shaping the arc of a set — building peaks, creating valleys, and leaving dancers wanting more.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

